<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1436,263,570]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,261,263,289]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Content:</emphasis>
Two subspecies restricted to central-southern and southern 
<collectingCountry box="[1004,1071,264,290]" name="Chile" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Chile</collectingCountry>
. In a recent study, PincheiraDonoso &amp; Núñez (2005) recognized these two taxa as geographical populations of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Hellmich" authorityYear="1932" box="[1156,1429,304,329]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chillanensis">
<emphasis box="[1156,1429,304,329]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Liolaemus chillanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, providing full species category to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schulte et al." authorityYear="2004" box="[563,713,344,369]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="monticola">
<emphasis box="[563,713,344,369]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. monticola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the same work, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Nunez" box="[958,1375,344,370]" firstAuthor="Pincheira-Donoso" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" refId="ref69923" refString="Pincheira-Donoso, D. &amp; Nunez, H. (2005) Las especies chilenas del genero Liolaemus (Iguania, Tropiduridae, Liolaeminae). Taxonomia, sistematica y evolucion, Publicacion Ocasional del Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, Santiago, 486 pp." type="book" year="2005">Pincheira-Donoso &amp; Núñez (2005)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Hellmich" box="[285,604,384,409]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="chillanensis" subSpecies="chillanensis">
<emphasis box="[285,604,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. chillanensis chillanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Hellmich" box="[662,985,384,409]" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="chillanensis" subSpecies="villaricensis">
<emphasis box="[662,985,384,409]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. chillanensis villaricensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
might be a single taxon (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Hellmich" authorityYear="1932" class="Reptilia" family="Liolaemidae" genus="Liolaemus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chillanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">L. chillanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) with no clear limits to be considered formal subspecies. Both populations not only exhibit substantial overlap of phenotypic traits, but also appear to have continuous geographical ranges. Therefore, their status need to be studied in more detail in order to determine their, if any, phylogenetic boundaries (see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Pincheira-Donoso" box="[151,448,544,570]" firstAuthor="Pincheira-Donoso" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref69397" refString="Pincheira-Donoso, D. (2003 b) Sistematica y biogeografia de Liolaemus altissimus araucaniensis Muller y Hellmich de Chile, y sus vinculaciones con la taxonomia de Liolaemus monticola chillanensis y Liolaemus monticola villaricensis (Iguania: Tropiduridae: Liolaeminae). Noticiario Mensual Museo Nacional de Historia Natural de Chile, 352, 1 - 8." type="journal article" year="2003" yearSuffix="b">Pincheira-Donoso 2003b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
